title: Perry Dam Race
description: The Perry Dam Training Series is Sunday March 13th and 20th at Rock Creek Park, Perry Kansas. This Classic Circuit Race has been in existence for 15+ years. The race is sponsored by Jim Whittaker and his Financial Strategies team. www.jimwhittaker.nylagents.com  Revolution Racing Event Promotions www.revolution-racing.com  Junior Entry Fees are sponsored by the Keen Wealth Advisors.
course: Course is a paved 5 mile loop with an uphill finish. It offers a .5 mile climb that is gradual at the bottom and steeper at the top, a fast downhill, and flat cross winds. It suits a strong all-rounder as much as a climber. A challenging course that will build your fitness for late Spring and Summer events. The course is NOT closed but corners will be supervised.
registration: Registration is race day only and is $28 for all categories except for juniors which is $5. Registration opens at 9:15am and closes at 9:45am and then 45 minutes prior to each event and for a period of 30 minutes thus closing 15 minutes before each race.
notes: The Perry Dam Training Series will offer series awards for the top 3 of each category. Point Scale is as follows: 1st - 10 points, 2nd - 8 points, 3rd - 7 points, 4th - 6 points, 5th - 5 points, 6th - 4 points, 7th - 3 points, 8th - 2 points - Participation Points for all races but DNS - 1 point Ties broken by final race placing.
directions: The course is approximately 4.5 miles northwest of Perry, Kansas. From Topeka take Highway 24 east to Thompsonville Road. Go North and follow the signs to the race headquarters located in Rock Creek Park. From Lawrence take highway 24 west to Thompsonville Road, and follow the signs to the race headquarters.

title: Rage Against the Chainring
description: Rage Against the Chainring is a gravel race series consisting of four races held annually, on courses around Wichita, Kansas.
course:
Courses consist of two 25 mile loops that start and finish at the same location.

There is a 25 mile short course option as well.

title: Jayhawk Cycling Classic
description: The Jayhawk Classic is a two day collegiate race weekend March 12-13 held in Lawrence, Kansas. Amateur categories will be able to race in the Saturday criterium held on KU's West Campus, but not Sunday.

Tour de Trees
description: The 2nd Annual Tour de Trees, a benefit for the Bartlett Arboretum is October 23, 2016.  Rain date is October 30, 2016.  The event this year is starting and ending at the Arboretum.  2 loops, each approximately 25 miles.  The 25 mile loop rides to Oxford Kansas and back to Belle Plaine.  The 2 loop leaves the Arb and is another 25 miles north of town.  There will be 1 rest stop in Oxford, and one on the 2nd loop.  Tour De Trees is in conjunction with the 3rd Annual Eco Fest at the Arb.  We invite you to enjoy the afternoon at the Arb.  Join us in riding the bicycle powered PA system to keep the music going!  Registration includes souvenir Tour De Trees T shirt, admission to the Arb and a meal voucher to one of the food trucks at Eco Fest.
directions: Event starting at the Bartlett Arboretum in Belle Plaine Kansas
